metadata.name: life shaping itself in a whirling universe
metadata.description:
We,as a existing being in this vast universe,always confront confusing, foggy scenarios as well as starry moments in life.
We can't actually see through what life wants to tell us but just walk towards where we decide to take the next step. However, it is indeed throughout these abundant things around us and our relationship with them to let us clarify the truth, which we embody and experience. And at the end, our footprints form a distinct shape,like a wing.

metadata.name: Cycles
metadata.description:
Cycles is a study on perception of the movement induced by the juxtaposition of color cycles.
It is made of custom Javascript code and rendered using WebGL.

The size of the cells is determined at mint time.
The grid then adapts to the resolution by changing the number of cells, so you can enjoy the piece in full screen mode.

- Type "P" to pause the animation.
- Type "S" to save the current frame.

Cycles implements the "Add to home screen" feature (A2HS), so you can display your edition on your phone with a touch of the finger.
Open the ipfs file and click "Add to home screen" in your mobile browser.

@unrulyunroll 03/17/2022

metadata.name: Adventure
metadata.description:
â€˜Adventureâ€™, inspired by â€˜Soundscapeâ€™ of â€˜The Paper Craneâ€™, brings to fxhash the recreation of landscapes with the use of the lines.

What are the lines?

A line is a continuous brand with a longer length than width, made on a surface, by a moving point. It's one of the seven basic elements of art.

How can the lines be?

Lines can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal; straight or curves, thick or thin. But also simple or single-trace, perceived by a glance or composed of fragments of two or more lines, which to visualize them must displace our eyes in several directions.

Artwork (PNG layers). Randomization is powered by PureSpider template.

metadata.name: Physarum Logo
metadata.description:
These past few months have been a great experience and with the beta ending, I wanted to create a piece to thank all collectors and pay tribute to this great platform. 

The piece is based on a physarum simulation with a couple of tweaks, such as continuous behavioural changes and an extra information layer that further manipulates the physarum.

There are ~262k particles simulated in parallel, so it is quite GPU heavy. 

Each piece features one of 12 different colour pallets, the text and a couple of cell-like bodies running around the screen.

Controls: 
S - Save image
H - Hide Text
Click/Touch - Spawn particles

Disclaimer: This is nothing official by the platform itself, merely a tribute by an artist and fan. 

With all that said: Thank you to everyone, and see you in 1.0 !

metadata.description:
fx(Toadz) CC are Cryptoadz (cryptoadz.io) on fx(hash) which can change color. Using the power of CC0 artwork, you can now acquire a toad on the Tezos blockchain. This time it comes with a monochrome variant.

Each toad is randomly generated at mint, trait rarities are based on the tx hash from mint and do not match "real" toadz rarities. The final distribution of attributes cannot be known until all fx(Toadz) are minted.

Artwork (PNG layers) is courtesy of the Cryptoadz team and toadztoolz.com (via CC0/public domain), randomization is powered by PureSpider template and the fx(rand) on fx(hash) platform.

metadata.name: PSYCHOGEOGRAPHIC MAP
metadata.description:
The psychogeographic maps are a proposal for the construction of an artistic journey guided by the principle of walking as a poetic practice that arises through the Situationist artistic movement in the years 1952-1975 in France. The Situationist proposal was to experience a journey without a defined direction in order to make this journey a work of art, an artistic, poetic, social and personal experience.

This map will guide your luck, choose or be chosen by the lines that will guide your next journey, maybe these lines will lead you to your love, your success, your true life, or maybe they will lead you to failure, you will only know if you decide to have your own psychogeographic map of your next journey.

I know I will use all the money from the sale of this work to travel, I also don't know how far they will take me, but I will get there.



The journey is inevitable and where you can get with it is unimaginable, maybe you get there only psychogeographically, but I recommend that you also get there geographically.

Maps and Draw Layers in PNG using @purespider's open Code. 

2022- CarÃ³, Brazil (for a while)
